that a way keep all local versions to solve all conflicts?


ChatGPT said:
ğŸ”¥ Yes, absolutely â€” if you're confident your local versions are correct and you just want to keep everything from your PC, you can tell Git:

â€œResolve all merge conflicts by keeping my local version of every file.â€

âœ… Command to Keep All Local Versions
Run this:

bash
Copy
Edit
git checkout --ours .
That means:

â€œFor every conflicted file, use my (local/PC) version.â€

Then:

bash
Copy
Edit
git add .
git commit -m "Resolved all conflicts by keeping local versions"
git push -u origin main
ğŸ§  Why this works

Git Ref	Meaning
--ours	Your local version (what's on your PC)
--theirs	The version from GitHub (remote)
So git checkout --ours . tells Git:

Use all my PC files and discard the remote ones for this merge.


